<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>git on Bossagyu Blog</title><link>https://bossagyu.com/en/tags/git/</link><description>Recent content in git on Bossagyu Blog</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en-US</language><lastBuildDate>Tue, 16 Apr 2024 23:16:25 +0900</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://bossagyu.com/en/tags/git/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Applying gitignore Globally</title><link>https://bossagyu.com/en/blog/025-git-ignore/</link><pubDate>Tue, 16 Apr 2024 23:16:25 +0900</pubDate><guid>https://bossagyu.com/en/blog/025-git-ignore/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="overview">Overview&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>This article simplifies the process of adding directories like &lt;code>.idea&lt;/code> which are automatically generated by IDEs to &lt;code>.gitignore&lt;/code> by applying the settings globally, rather than per project.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="how-to-apply-gitignore-globally">How to Apply gitignore Globally&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>Creating a &lt;code>.gitignore_global&lt;/code> file and registering it with &lt;code>core.excludesfile&lt;/code> is a common method, but git by default looks for ignore settings in &lt;code>~/.config/git/ignore&lt;/code>.&lt;br>
By placing your ignore settings into this file, you can apply them across all projects.&lt;/p>
&lt;h3 id="creating-the-directory">Creating the Directory&lt;/h3>
&lt;p>First, create the directory if it doesn&amp;rsquo;t already exist:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;div class="chroma">
&lt;table class="lntable">&lt;tr>&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code>&lt;span class="lnt">1
&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>
&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-shell" data-lang="shell">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">mkdir -p ~/.config/git/
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;h3 id="creating-the-ignore-file">Creating the ignore File&lt;/h3>
&lt;p>Next, create the ignore file and add the patterns you want to ignore universally:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;div class="chroma">
&lt;table class="lntable">&lt;tr>&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code>&lt;span class="lnt">1
&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>
&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-shell" data-lang="shell">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">vim ~/.config/git/ignore
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;p>Add entries like so:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;div class="chroma">
&lt;table class="lntable">&lt;tr>&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code>&lt;span class="lnt">1
&lt;/span>&lt;span class="lnt">2
&lt;/span>&lt;span class="lnt">3
&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>
&lt;td class="lntd">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-fallback" data-lang="fallback">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">.idea/
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">*.log
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">node_modules/
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>&lt;p>This setup negates the need to add extra configurations in &lt;code>.gitconfig&lt;/code> which would be necessary if using &lt;code>.gitignore_global&lt;/code>, making it a simpler and cleaner solution.&lt;/p>
